  "text": "Isolation of Tropomyosin-enriched Microfilaments and AIpha-actinin-enriched Microfilaments from CEF Cells: The microfilament isolation method was essentially similar to that described previously [CITATION_1] . As outlined in Fig . 1 , CEF cells (20-30 plates of 100-mm culture dishes) after washing three times with phosphate-buffered saline were treated with Triton X-100/glycerol solution (0 .05% Triton X-100, 0.1 M PIPES, 5 mM MgC12 , 0.2 mM EGTA, 4 M glycerol) for 2 min at room temperature . After washing three times with phosphate-buffered saline containing 5 MM MgC12 and 0 .2 mM EGTA, the Triton/glycerol-insoluble residues were scraped off from dishes and homogenized in 20 mM phosphate buffer, pH 7 .0, containing 100 mM NaCl, 5 mM MgC12, 5 mM ATP, 0.2 mM EGTA, and 5 mM phenylmethyl sulfonyl fluoride . The total homogenates were then centrifuged at 12,800 g for 15 min to remove a majority of the intermediate filaments and nuclei . The supernatant (denoted as Sup-1) was incubated with either onetenth volume of antitropomyosin monoclonal antibody (LKC16) or one-fifth volume of anti-alpha-actinin monoclonal antibody (JLN20) for 1 h at 4°C . The resultant immunoprecipitates were collected and washed three times in phosphate-buffered saline containing 5111M M9C12 and 0.2 mM EGTA by lowspeed centrifugation (12,800 g for 5 min). The final pellet was designated as either tropomyosin-enriched microfilaments (TM,-MF) or alpha-actinin-enriched microflaments (aA,-MF), respectively . In some experiments, the anti-'Abbreviations used in this paper: CEF, chicken embryo cells ; DME, Dulbecco's modified Eagle's medium . body supernatant was further precipitated with either anti-alpha-actinin (JLN20), or antitropomyosin (LCK16) antibody, respectively. The resultant pellets were designated as alpha-actinin-enriched microfilaments after the removal of tropomyosin-enriched microfilaments (aA2-MF) or tropomyosinenriched microfilaments after the removal of alpha-actinin-enriched microfilaments (TM2-MF) . In experiments where the microfilaments were precipitated by simultaneous addition of both LCK16 and JLN20 antibodies, the microfilaments were denoted as tropomyosin and alpha-actinin-enriched microfilaments ([TM+aA]-MF).",
